values:
Howdy all, quicky update and compressing the last few months down:

Got my wishlist up and sent present on, hoping they like it

Signing on is a bitch, assholes want to start it a week late cos I got 20 hours holiday pay...that's like 2 days to me

Work as ever is hard to find, although Nintendo are hiring and I'd take the "Shigeru's Personal Cock Sucker" for a job there, it is in Germany though but I'd be willing to move

World of Warcraft has stolen my life, it'll be all worth it when I can make my first robotic attack chicken though.

Going to an audition for a Murder Mystery on monday, dibs on the Dead Guy...well I am a stiff actor...*sound of two drums and a cymbal falling off a cliff*

And last but not least...MERRY CHRISTMAS ^^

Jim

Well I buggered this up didn't I, I've messed up several units so I can't pass with a BSC Hons anymore but if I re-submit my 3D Animation (they messed up and it should have passed, damn messed up uni CD writers) and add some extra bits to my systems engeneering they'll still give me a plain BSC.

So in the end I may wrangle a degree out of this after all :)

Work going good, they've lost my pay slip though which I really want so I can check my tax :/

Anyway tis goin okies, c ya round

Jim

And I'm not touching the other one

Ok, it's been tiring for the last few days as have been working arse off but it's all in so now only the stuff after easter to hand in...YAY

Although I belive the fatigue has got to my brain.  With a few guys on the PSTP forum (new webcomic), we've been working on a MeMe to over-run the interweb, he has already spread to Newgrounds and is freaking out people world wide.

http://www.pressstarttoplay.net/forums/viewtopic.php?t=2513

If your curious I'm Vigilante :p

Don't ask me why, started off as one cricle, i gave it eyes and then it grew...

http://i51.photobucket.com/albums/f369/Vigilante151/Chibis.jpg

And does anyone know what I should do with them? I wanna colour them in (on the computer) but I'm not sure how to go about it

Good news, I've been accepted at Primrose Vally as a Bar Man! I know it's not using my degree to it's full potential :p but my view is that computing changes all the time, but people will always need someone to fry their chips and pour their pints so I'll always have a back-up.

So hopefully the tourists will not send me insane and I can get some Bar experience under my belt :)

Slacker Ninja Away!

Damn I feel buggered, went paintballing on sunday with a group of Games Computing guys and my legs are still asking for payback today.  Got there at 9 and then spent untill 4:30 running around, climbing up stuff and getting shot at (apart from one time where I had to hold the flag till the end of the game, scariest 5 minutes of hiding in a corner of my life).  But all in all had a great time, was like playing Battlefield 2 but hurt more :p.

After that, popped back for an hour before going to meet them at the Big Wok where i managed to eat an entire plate of food with no chips or prawn crackers in sight!  Scared myself too...

Got up Monday (after an hour of willing my legs to move) and remembered I had Salsa that night.  Now if I've learnt anything over the last few days it was that Salsa is very hard when your falling asleep and your legs are on strike, meaning my soft flowing movements quickly detiriated into toe crushing stomps.

So todays main activity is gonna be sitting around, waiting for my limbs to want to play ball again, and probably finding a couple more paintball bruises too.

Ninja away!

Work: Gone
Games: Donkey Konga 2 until my hands bleed!

Well i did it, i am now officially back within the ranks of the unemployed, i would have posted earlier but not had chance.  I went in on monday, picked up last weeks pay and left, was as easy as that.

So now apart from my mum finding countless things for me to do i'm free and counting the days till i return to Lincoln (although i'm now coming on the 5th so Mad can come to Filey before one of her many trips to spain)

C ya real soon

Jim

Work: A boiling mental tourture chamber
Games: Not had chance

I'm done, i'm through, kaput, finito.

I have had enough of that annoying bloody little cafe, let me walk you through the last couple of days at work i've done and you'll get the idea:

Tuesday Evening: Now before we start this you need to know but one thing, the fish fryer needs to be on 170 degrees while the chip fryer is on 150, tis a simple fact.

Now then, it's the end of a long 10 hour day at the cafe and yet again my boss come around the corner with the look of thunder on her face, she first accuses me of turning the fryers off, after proving to her that they are on she says they're at the wrong temperature (but atm they're at 170 and 150).

I tell her that's what i'm told to have them on, she then yells that i'm always blaming other people for my problems and she'll check herself with Bob (the guy who taught me how to fry).  She comes back and says they should be on 170 and 150 then walks off...

THAT'S WHAT THEY'RE ON YOU DOSY BITCH!!!!

This is just one example of the many times she has come looking for something wrong with my work, and with 5 different people telling me 5 different ways of doing things all the time it's easy for one of them to find something they think is wrong and make me feel stupid.

Thursday: Due to my work on the fryers being "unsatisfactory" i'm put on waiting duty, which i can do, but i had to at the same time try to teach this new dosy bint who's as much use as a chocolate teapot what to do, and of course when i tell her something someone else came along and told her different.  Now when i started and i did something wrong i got told off, when she does something wrong...i get told off...

...okay, anyone heard of justice over here...

finally i mistime the dishwasher after doing everything else right (i've not used it for 3 weeks, give me a break) i get shouted at, and i mean shouted.

The end result of this, i've decided to give 2 weeks notice on monday, i can't do it for another 6 weeks, that place is driving me mad, i've got my overdaft repayed, i've got the job on my CV, i dont need to go anymore.

And if they sack me there on the spot, tough shit, means i'll actually get some time to relax for a change, all my relatives agree that it sounds good so no backlash from parents either.  Also being that i plan to finish the weekend before August starts, instead of just dropping my stuff off when we get the house i can move in!

Right now though i'm just lookin forward to comin to Lincoln tomorrow, and also with the money i should be getting from lighthouse i'm gonna treat myself to a DS, will make me feel better anyway :D

C ya all tomorrow

Jim

Games: Apart from fish flipping, not much
Work: Every day seems to get longer

Heya all

Got some good news, i've got next friday and saturday off so i'm comin down to Lincoln for the weekend!!! Hurrah, i can finally escape from my work and parents for a bit! Who's gonna be down next weekend?

I hope to see everyone who's there when i go and also spend some much needed quality time with Mad, spoiling her rotten while i get the chance :)

Also and an odd side point, on a farm in turkey, 1500 sheep attempted a mass suicide and walked off a 15m cliff, one went and the other's just followed, but only the first 450 died cos all the others bounced of those that had already hit the bottom:

Baaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa...*split*
Baaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa...*split*
Baaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa...*boing*...baa?

c ya next week hopefully

Jim (Baa)

Games: Bad news-Zelda:twilight princess aint out till sept Good news: it looks smoother than greased silk ;)
Work: Tiring

Bugger Bugger Bugger and Damn!

As you might have guessed i've not passed yet, all my results are over 50 apart from this one which i got 29 for, originally we all thought this bit was only a part of another unit (which i got 68 in) but turns out this one bit of work was a stand alone unit!

As for everything else, i thought i should have ended up with a 2.1 but a few bad marks have brought me down to 57.1 or 58 as the uni always rounds up...i think.

anyway, here are my numbers:

54, 63, 52, 76 (Games Design, woot!), 50, 50, 50, 68, 68, and the bonus ball 29 (which i count as 40 in my calculations for when i pass)

I'm thinkin of bookin a week of at from August the 1st so i can get moved into the house, will anyone be down there for an obligatory piss up?

c ya soon

Jim

Gameplaying: Dance machine on sea front
Work: See Below
Time with Parents: Free alcohol and food, sweet!

Hey all, i've got some good news and some bad news:

Good-I've been moved to full time at my job, next week i'll be doing 45-50 hours, i may not be on minimum wage but it's still alot

Bad-This means that my attendance at the Harry Potter camp outside of Otticars may be tricky. Sorry :/

I'm not sure about this shift, i wasn't expecting to work so much, atm i'll get wendsday and sunday off, i'm thinkin that it'll be much more money, but i'm also worried i may not be able to handle it.

In other news, my wisdom teeth (wisdom? me?) are erupting so havin a fun time with those, also just been to watch my dad launch off in the local fishing competition, seeing all those boats heading off at once made me think of Wakey Races, was expecting Dick Dastardly to head out in front and set a trap for the others.

Talkin of Dick, if he can get far enough ahead in a race to set up to 3 traps for the other racers, taking alot of time to organise, how come he don't just head for the finish and win? Is it me?

Hope to see you all soon

Jim

Gameplaying: Compleated Mario 64 with mad before she left
Work: Read on...
Time with parents: usual, lots of coffee

Well first up some good news, they're hiring me full time at the cafe and i'm  goin on a rota next saturday! 15 hours a week min here i come!

But onto another topic, i have just realised today i have a shocking addiction...the 2p pusher machines in the arcades! whenever i'm down there i can't help but put more and more 2p's into the hungry automotons, yerning for the little cuddly toys inside that once i've go home mean nothing to me...the copper it stains my fingers a dark green and it can be smelt from meters away...

...I've started mugging small children for their change now to feed my needs...

but apart from that i'm ok, also looked at the games and i'm on the top 5 scoreboard for most of them now, just a few more to go :P

C Ya

Jim

Gameplaying: Lots of Mario 64
Work: Odd
Time with parents: Mainly Beaches
Time With Mads: YAY!

Well, must say that it was amazingly quiet yesterday, we think that everyone decided to bugger off to the sea side cos it was so sunny.

Mads has been with me since saturday! Couldn't stop clinging onto her for the first couple of days but cos i've been workin i'm gonna have to leave her with my parents.

c ya

jim

Work: Working on it
Time with Family: replacing time with friends and mad...sadly

WooHoo! Got a trial at the Chip Cafe down the road on Friday!  There are two other lasses up for the job who have trials on different days, but none of us apparently has prior experience so level playing field.

I know you all thought it'd be a bad idea me workin in a chippy as i'd get fed up of my main food group but it's more of a cafe and chips arn't the main fodder.  Also minimum of 15 hours a week through 3 shifts, at a place 1 min walk down road is not to be ignored.

If all else fails i'm signing up to a temp agency an monday so fingers crossed

Gameplaying: Very Laggy Harry
Work: When ya think it's all over...
Time with friends: Greatly missed
Time with Mads: Greatly missed, but moreso

Well got home yesterday, only to be told by my mum to sort out all my stuff on the spot! This is two years of collected junk we're talking about, and a mother who usually want's to throw everything you like away and anything she can't she'll tidy away.

I've just rescued my Mew from her as she wished to dispose of it, but he is safe now.

As may be the case with many parents, my mum's idea of tidying away is putting things in places that you'll never look for thew item but she knows where they are, therefore you have to ask her and make her look like the only organised one in the house.

Also on my bed was a pile of job adverts, which i was set about calling today, luckly one was a temp agancy so i've set and interview date with them for next week, that'll give me a slight rest anyway.

Don't get me wrong, i love my mum to bits but she want's to go at 100mph all the time.

I'm of to sort my CV out, then she'll have to find something else to pester me about (the usuall one when she can't find anything elseis that i smell, she once said i smelt 5 minutes after i got out of a bath!).

C ya

Jim

Gameplaying: Fair amount, mixed between PC and console Work: All done WooHoo! Time with Friends: Ok, resting for the big piss up later in the week Time with Mad: On the rise thanks to less work Well at last everything for this year is done, but let us travel back to yesterday, a young student named Jim is heading for his appointment at the hospital... *sholedo sholedo sholedo (just try and say it, it does work)* The doctors was ok, he was a no nosense kind of guy that rattled orders off like a machine gun and didn't actually care for my well being, for example: doctor: "lift your leg up for me please" me with cramp in leg: "ow, it hurts!" doctor: "suffer" after that he sent me for a heart scan and a BLOOD TEST! (phobia of needles kicking in about...now) Noooooooooooooooo! every time i go to the hospital they find an excuse to stick something in me. I though ok, if i get in quick and get this done i'll be ok... ...2 and a half hours later... ...I'm finally leaving the hospital with my puncture wound. Now back to today The presentation went well, apart from the beginning, where the one of the guys introduced us and didn't mention me or what i did (yes it's the same guy i've been throwing out of windows alot lately), i had to pipe up to get mentioned and thats most likely dropped our presentation mark! But on another note the tutor liked our game alot (he kept mentioning how he liked this and that throughout the presentation), we'd got in first so we set the benchmark and even better, the group who went in next had a level you could complete in LESS THAN A MINUTE! So not only are we memorable cos we were good and first, the next game he had to compare us too was shite! Roll out the 1st please sir! Jim

Gameplaying: Been in the lab but not a game was played
Work: ...don't...ask...
Time with friends: Donna's parents keep taking her away earlier and bringing her back later every week
Time with Mads: gonna have some soon :D

Well, i've just handed in my work today with the rest of my group, was very close, the lady was just closing our faculty as it struck 3.  Was only cos we were running that the momentum carried us through the door (I'm sure they'll be able to fix it).

I got in at 9am and started work with them until the deadline, what? you think i mean 9am THIS morning?!?

I HAVE BEEN IN THAT F*CKING SH*T HOLE FOR THE LAST 30 HOURS!!!!!!!

It didn't start that well, i'd decided that I was not going to get stressed like the rest of my group do...sadly one of them made a joke in poor taste involving my dad and "kiddie fiddling"...

...that was that out the window...

...shortly followed by him...

the worst thing is that between them, my group can best me in any form of implementation in half life, thus meaning most the jobs go to them, i wouldn't mind this but i feel left out in the cold and useless, then one of them (the one metioned above) had the cheek to say i wasn't doing enough work...

...que second smashed window...

we were kicked out at 12 (the guard didn't really want to, there were 15 people in there not too happy about leaving), we just hid round the corner for 30 min and ninja'd our way back into the building again.

There we stayed (well until the coffee shop in the atrium opened at 8 at least, was a horrible sight seeing geeks lined up waitin for their caffeine hit like crack heads in a dark alley), the "Time Remaining" was going down much faster that the "Work Remaining" again and as i said above it was a very close call.

Well i'm home, i got out of there asap and now i'm just waiting for mad to turn up and give me a cuddle to make me feel better...

...untill i remember we're preparing for the presentation tomorrow...

...urge to kill, at the same high it's been at for the last 30 hours...

I wanna hug ='(

Jim

Gameplaying: Fair bit, some in lab during work breaks :p Work: My "Time Remaining" is going down faster than my "Work Remaining" Time with friends: Many a drop of alcahol has passed my lips in their company Time with Mads: Great sunday in alone together :D *Stealth Mode Activated* Currently in lab, but the media building is closed today as it's bank holiday, it pays to look over faculty members shoulders when they're entering the door codes. Well i think it's daft, we have hand-in's on friday and they close the building for the day *Lie Mode Activated* but we don't really need the time, they don't change the assignments last minute, we don't need to be in 24 hours a day to get near a 1st. *Lie Mode Deactivated* I'm actually surprised i got in here, with all the cameras and the dime-a-day guard to the room that has the a tom of computing equiptment, there isn't even a camera in here! Shit, i think in hear someone comin, if they come for me my code-name is Grandmaster Wallaby, you may contact me by the radio i hid in my Game Cube. Ninja Away

Gameplaying: Some thanks to late night FF6
Work: The people in the lab are discussing forms of suicide
Time with friends: Only thing keeping me half sane
Time with Maddy: WAY too little

I'm really missing Mad at the mo, with all the work and exams goin on we haven't really been together on our own much and with the summer holidays comin up there's not much time left.  I know i won't be able to go places cos my mum's told me i am getting a job, even if it's McDonald's or the local chippy.

I don't wanna go home, i'm so used to seeing everyone every day (and it's kinda hard to get away from Donna, I've tried explosives and fire but neither work, thus my repitoir is spent). My parents are usually telling me i have to do something and if by some mirical they're not, it don't seem right.

If anyone happens to head for Filey for their holiday come the 1 mile out your way to Hunmanby to see me but be careful, they have this thing about people who arn't "local"

Have a Good Summer

Jim

Current info:

Gameplaying- Too little at the mo
Work- Too Much
Time with Friends- Tons, Yay me

Hello one and all...what? You want me to write something interesting,ok.

Well currently i'm doing work which probs should have been done months ago, but hey i'm games computing, if your not doing at least some work in the last week your too far ahead.

Looking forward to attempting to burn food over charcoal tonight, in my attempts to be a manly man i may cause both food poisoning and 1st degree burns all in one night so i'd have a St Johns standin by.

Fave game atm, Final Fantasy 6 when i can fit it in, tis all the more fun with donna playing with me shouting "DIE BASTARDS DIE!" and "WHY WONT THE BLITZ WORK DAMMIT!", adds that little bit of violence every game needs, even tetris has the destruction of innocent blocks.

Well i'm off now to drink tons of coffee in an attempt to get both my maths done and some Games Design, although this will have the side effect of making me hyper while barbecuing, i'd have 999 on speed dial.

C ya

Jim
